 top predator on a rain forest understory plant community (2004) Ecology, 85, pp. 2144-52; Low, C., Connor, E.F., Birds have no impact on folivorous insect guilds on a montane willow (2003) Oikos, 103, pp. 579-89; McQuillan, P.B., Nothofagus (Fagaceae) and its invertebrate fauna - An overview and preliminary synthesis (1993) Biol. J. Linn. Soc. Lond., 49, pp. 317-54; Marquis, R.J., Whelan, C.J., Insectivorous birds increase growth of white oak through consumption of leaf-chewing insects (1994) Ecology, 75, pp. 2007-14; Mattson, W.J., Haack, R.A., The role of drought in outbreaks of plant-eating insects (1987) BioScience, 37, pp. 110-18; Mazía, C.N., Kitzberger, T., Chaneton, E.J., Interannual changes in folivory and bird insectivory along a natural productivity gradient in northern Patagonian forests (2004) Ecography, 27, pp. 29-40; Meserve, P.L., Kelt, D.A., Milstead, W.B., Gutierrez, J.R., Thirteen years of shifting top-down and bottom-up control (2003) BioScience, 53, pp. 633-46; Mooney, K.A., Tritrophic effects of birds and ants on a canopy food web, tree growth, and phytochemistry (2007) Ecology, 88, pp. 2005-14; Murakami, M., Nakano, S., Species-specific bird functions in a canopy food-web (2000) Proc. R. Soc. Lond. B. Biol. Sci., 267, pp. 1597-601; Oksanen, L., Fretwell, S.D., Arruda, J., Niemela, P., Exploitation ecosystems in gradients of primary productivity (1981) Am. Nat., 118, pp. 240-61; Osenberg, C.W., Sarnelle, O., Cooper, S.D., Effect size in ecological experiments: The application of biological models in meta-analysis (1997) Am. Nat., 150, pp. 798-812; Ovadia, O., Schmitz, O.J., Weather variation and trophic interaction strength: Sorting the signal from the noise (2004) Oecologia, 140, pp. 398-406; Pace, M.L., Cole, J.J., Carpenter, S.R., Kitchell, J.K., Trophic cascades revealed in diverse ecosystems (1999) Trends Ecol. Evol., 14, pp. 483-8; Parry, D., Spence, J.R., Volney, W.J.A., Responses of natural enemies to experimentally increased populatio